Key Match Events: Barrow (62') scored the winning goal for Gambia
Ceesay (30'), Fadera (38') received yellow cards for Gambia
Patrick Laiton (27'), Caddy (40') received yellow cards for Madagascar
Pre-Game Insights: Gambia dominated play in the last match but Madagascar have proven time and again of late that they are a difficult side to defeat
Gambia's new boss Johnny McKinstry has seen his side only beaten by Gabon and Tunisia since his arrival
Madagascar have only lost three of their last 10 games (W4 D3 L3)
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Stade Ben Ahmed El Abdi in Morocco due to Gambia's stadiums failing to meet FIFA standards
Musa Barrow is likely to be brought back into the starting 11 for Gambia after a fairly underwhelming performance from Muhammed Badamosi last time out
Others: Gambia's Yankuba Minteh has been the main man in recent times, playing a role in three of the last four goals the side have scored
Madagascar's Nicolas Fontaine is likely to return to the starting lineup this week to partner Louis Demoleon in central defence
